WEBVTT

00:04.657 --> 00:05.970
WOLOWITZ:
What are you doing?

00:05.971 --> 00:08.772
Pigeon check for Sheldon.

00:08.774 --> 00:10.807
North side's all clear!

00:10.809 --> 00:13.110
Great. Let's look
at some planets!

00:13.112 --> 00:16.113
Hey, why'd you lug your
telescope all the way over here?

00:16.114 --> 00:17.748
Leonard has one
in our apartment.

00:17.750 --> 00:19.483
Yeah, I'm gonna
use Leonard's.

00:19.485 --> 00:23.020
Might as well hold my hand
up like this and squint.

00:23.022 --> 00:25.556
I don't know.
It seemed pretty good.

00:25.558 --> 00:27.524
You know, once
when the cable went out,

00:27.526 --> 00:29.326
I watched an entire episode
of <i>The Bachelor</i>

00:29.328 --> 00:32.162
on a TV across the street.

00:32.164 --> 00:34.398
This one's more
of a professional model.

00:34.400 --> 00:36.033
So was the girl he picked!

00:36.035 --> 00:40.837
This baby's got a ten-inch
diameter with f/10 ACF optics.

00:40.839 --> 00:42.272
WOLOWITZ:
And tonight

00:42.274 --> 00:45.175
Mercury is
at its highest elongation.

00:45.177 --> 00:50.747
It makes far-away things seem
close, and Mercury is a planet.

00:50.749 --> 00:53.617
I know Mercury is a planet.

00:53.619 --> 00:56.019
But the-the other
thing was helpful.

00:56.021 --> 00:58.422
Oh. Look at that.

00:58.424 --> 01:01.024
- Neil Gaiman tweeted about my store!
- What did he say?

01:01.026 --> 01:02.659
Uh, "Next time
you're in Pasadena,

01:02.661 --> 01:04.227
"check out The Comic Center.

01:04.230 --> 01:06.029
"Great vibe,
old school,

01:06.031 --> 01:08.065
the owner really knows
his stuff."

01:08.067 --> 01:09.933
Isn't that amazing?

01:09.935 --> 01:12.202
Well, uh, it's no <i>Sandman,</i>
but I guess we can't expect

01:12.204 --> 01:14.738
everything he writes
to be a masterpiece.

01:14.740 --> 01:16.340
When was he in your store?

01:16.342 --> 01:19.209
I have no idea.
I think I would remember that.

01:19.211 --> 01:22.646
Obviously, vibranium is the
most powerful metal in comics.

01:22.648 --> 01:24.681
What, more powerful
than adamantium?

01:24.683 --> 01:26.283
He's right.

01:26.285 --> 01:28.885
Wolverine's claws,
Ultron's outer shell.

01:28.887 --> 01:30.354
Need I go on?

01:30.356 --> 01:32.889
You don't need to,
but you probably will.

01:34.093 --> 01:36.860
What about Wonder
Woman's bracelets?

01:36.862 --> 01:38.161
Good point.

01:38.163 --> 01:41.865
Strong as a metal and
fierce as a fashion choice.

01:41.867 --> 01:43.200
GAIMAN:
You know,

01:43.202 --> 01:44.635
Thor's hammer's
pretty powerful,

01:44.637 --> 01:47.471
and in the comics,
it's made out of enchanted uru.

01:47.473 --> 01:49.706
Uh, yeah, I think
it's the enchantment

01:49.708 --> 01:51.708
that's powerful,
not the uru,

01:51.710 --> 01:54.745
but, uh, thanks for playing.

01:56.548 --> 01:58.915
Oh, man, I can't believe
Neil Gaiman came in,

01:58.917 --> 01:59.990
and we weren't even there.

01:59.991 --> 02:02.991
